In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 26, 2015, as a National Day of Thanksgiving. He highlights the history of Thanksgiving, tracing it back to the early 17th century when the Pilgrims arrived in Plymouth and were aided by the indigenous Wampanoag people. The President acknowledges the challenges faced by the Pilgrims and the importance of their fellowship and gratitude for a bountiful harvest. He also recognizes the tradition of giving and the selflessness of the American people. President Obama encourages the nation to come together and give thanks for what they have received, appreciate those who enrich their lives, and share their blessings with others.